uploads/2009/01/end-of-the-line1.jpg\" alt=\"end of the line\" title=\"end of the line\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-16\" />The End of the Line, a film that documents overfishing, <a href=\"http://endoftheline.com/blog/archives/99\">premiered today at the Sundance Film Festival</a>.  <em>Sea Around Us</em> Project members Daniel Pauly and Rashid Sumaila take leading roles in this documentary based on <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/End-Line-Overfishing-Changing-World/dp/0091897815\">Charles Clover\'s book with the same title</a>.\r\n\r\n<object width=\"560\" height=\"340\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/QWB8KJ1aIJ4&hl=en&fs=1&\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/QWB8KJ1aIJ4&hl=en&fs=1&\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"560\" height=\"340\"></embed></object>.','End of the Line Premiere','','publish','open','open','','end-of-the-line-premiere','','\nhttp://endoftheline.com/blog/archives/99','2009-10-03 10:05:19','2009-10-03 17:05:19','',0,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/?p=11',0,'post','',0),(13,2,'2009-10-03 10:01:48','2009-10-03 17:01:48','','end of the line','','inherit','open','open','','end-of-the-line','','','2009-10-03 10:01:48','2009-10-03 17:01:48','',11,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/end-of-the-line.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(16,2,'2009-10-03 10:04:49','2009-10-03 17:04:49','','end of the line','','inherit','open','open','','end-of-the-line-2','','','2009-10-03 10:04:49','2009-10-03 17:04:49','',11,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/end-of-the-line1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(20,2,'1999-01-01 00:00:33','1999-01-01 07:00:33','<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1929\" title=\"200px-Daniel_Pauly_Pauly_Symposium\" src=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/1999/01/200px-Daniel_Pauly_Pauly_Symposium1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"311\" />\r\n\r\nBorn in France and raised in Switzerland, Daniel Pauly studied in Germany, where he acquired a doctorate in fisheries biology in 1979, from the University of Kiel. He did his first intercontinental travel in 1971 (from Germany to Ghana for field work related to his Masters) and has since experienced a multitude of countries, cultures, and modes of exploiting aquatic ecosystems in Africa, Asia, Oceania and the Americas. This perspective allowed him to develop tools for managing data-sparse fisheries, as prevailed for example in the Philippines, where Dr. Pauly worked through the 1980s and early 1990s.\r\n\r\nIn 1994, Dr. Pauly became a Professor at the University of British Columbia Fisheries Centre, and was its Director from 2003 to 2008. In 1999, Daniel Pauly founded, and since leads, a large research project devoted to identifying and quantifying global fisheries trends, funded by the Pew Charitable Trusts and called The Sea Around Us after Rachel Carson’s 1951 bestselling book. Daniel Pauly is also co-founder of <a href=\"http://fishbase.org/\">FishBase.org</a>, the online encyclopedia of more than 30,000 fish species, and he has helped develop the widely-used Ecopath modeling software. He is the author or co-author of more than 500 scientific and other articles, books and book chapters on fish, fisheries and related topics. Two of news books, reflecting his current interests were published in 2010: “Five Easy Pieces: Reporting on the Global Impact of Fisheries” and “Gasping Fish and Panting Squids: Oxygen, Temperature and the Growth of Water-Breathing Animals”. For more about Daniel Pauly’s work and for a full list and access to his publications, <a href=\"http://www.fisheries.ubc.ca/members/dpauly/\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a>.','Daniel Pauly - Principal Investigator','','publish','closed','open','','daniel-pauly'