ove.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(474,2,'2009-11-19 20:56:55','2009-11-20 03:56:55','','Sarika','','inherit','closed','open','','sarika','','','2009-11-19 20:56:55','2009-11-20 03:56:55','',0,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/Sarika.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(481,2,'2009-08-19 22:46:55','2009-08-20 05:46:55','<!--StartFragment--><a href=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/ashley.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-482\" title=\"ashley\" src=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/ashley-227x300.jpg\" alt=\"ashley\" width=\"227\" height=\"300\" /></a>Ashley is a postdoctoral-fellow with the <em>Sea Around Us</em> Project at the Fisheries Centre, and is working with Dr. Daniel Pauly and other project members. Ashley received her BSc in Zoology from the University of Florida. After spending a year working for a marine conservation organization on Maui, she began a PhD program in Marine Biology and Fisheries at the Rosenstiel School of Marine and Atmospheric Science at the University of Miami in Florida. Under the guidance of Dr. Jerald Ault, Ashley’s dissertation research focused on the use of two alternative multispecies modeling frameworks to evaluate the dynamic interactions between predator and prey populations, and to understand the influence of fisheries and environmental temperature change on predator-prey and food chain communities. In addition to her dissertation research, Ashley participated in aerial surveys of boater use in Everglades National Park, and was a research scuba diver for the Florida Keys Multi-Agency Reef Visual Census Study. Throughout her student career, she remained actively involved in secondary and post-secondary education, working as a graduate-level teaching assistant, high school biology teacher, math and science tutor, as well as a field-based environmental educator.\r\n\r\n<!--EndFragment-->','Ashley McCrea Strub - Post-Doc','','draft','closed','open','','ashley-mccrea-strub-post-doc','','','2015-01-16 17:38:18','2015-01-17 00:38:18','',0,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/?p=481',0,'post','',0),(482,2,'2009-11-19 22:48:42','2009-11-20 05:48:42','','ashley','','inherit','closed','open','','ashley','','','2009-11-19 22:48:42','2009-11-20 05:48:42','',481,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/ashley.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(485,2,'1999-01-01 00:00:57','1999-01-01 07:00:57','<a href=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/1999/06/rashid.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-492\" title=\"rashid\" src=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/1999/06/rashid-188x300.jpg\" alt=\"rashid\" width=\"188\" height=\"300\" /></a>Rashid Sumaila is Associate Professor, Director of the Fisheries Centre, and Director of the Fisheries Economics Research Unit at UBC Fisheries Centre. He has also been an active and key member of the <em>Sea Around Us</em> Project since its inception in 1999. He specializes in bioeconomics, marine ecosystem valuation and the analysis of global issues such as fisheries subsidies, IUU (Illegal, Unreported and Unregulated) fishing and the economics of high and deep seas fisheries. Rashid has experience working in fisheries and natural resource projects in Norway, Canada and the North Atlantic region, Namibia and the Southern African region, Ghana and the West African region and Hong Kong and the South China Sea. He has published articles in several journals including <em>Nature</em>, <em>Journal of Environmental Economics and Management, Journal of Bioeconomics, Land Economics, ICES Journal of Marine Science, Environmental and Resource Economics and Ecological Economics</em>. Rashid’s work has generated a great deal of interest, and has been cited by, among others, <em>the Economist, the Boston Globe, the International Herald Tribune and the Vancouver Sun</em>.  For more about his list and for his publications, <a href=\"http://www.fisheries.ubc.ca/members/rsumaila/\">click here</a>.','Rashid Sumaila – Associated Faculty','','publish','closed','open','','rashid-sumaila-faculty','','','2012-11-19 09:50:42','2012-11-19 16:50:42','',0,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/?p=485',0,'post','',0),(487,2,'2009-11-20 18:06:23','2009-11-21 01:06:23','','MeganBailey','','inherit','closed','open','','meganbailey','','','2009-11-20 18:06:23','2009-11-21 01:06:23','',0,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/MeganBailey.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(492,2,'2009-11-20 18:22:56','2009-11-21 01:22:56','','rashid','','inherit','closed','open','','rashid','','','2009-11-20 18:22:56','2009-11-21 01:22:56','',485,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/1999/06/rashid.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(513,2,'2009-11-21 11:03:04','2009-11-21 18:03:04','','arash_bio','','inherit','closed','open','','arash_bio','','','2009-11-21 11:03:04','2009-11-21 18:03:04','',259,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/arash_bio.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(520,2,'2009-11-25 12:17:12','2009-11-25 19:17:12','','marina','','inherit','closed','open','','marina','','','2009-11-25 12:17:12','2009-11-25 19:17:12','',0,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2008/08/marina.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(524,2,'1999-01-25 12:24:48','1999-01-25 19:24:48','Daniel Pauly\r\nc/o Grace Ong\r\nPhone: 604-822-0647\r\n\r\nVilly Christensen\r\nPhone: 604-822-5751\r\n\r\nRashid Sumaila\r\nPhone: 604-822-0224\r\n\r\nDirk Zeller\r\nPhone: 604-822-1950\r\n\r\nSea Around Us Project\r\nFisheries Centre\r\nAquatic Ecosystems Research Laboratory\r\nUniversity of British Columbia\r\n2202 Main Mall\r\nVancouver, B. C. Canada\r\nV6T 1Z4','Contact','','draft','closed','open','','contact','','','2010-01-10 17:53:41','2010-01-11 00:53:41','',0,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/?p=524',0,'post','',0),(526,2,'2009-01-25 12:25:05','2009-01-25 19:25:05','<t