dium wp-image-1006\" title=\"FisheriesCatch\" src=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/FisheriesCatch-300x157.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"157\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/FisheriesCatch.png\"></a>The <em>Sea Around Us </em>Project provides global marine fisheries landings spatially so we have an idea of which country caught what and where.  We have to keep the data updated, which takes a team of skilled people led by <a href=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/index.php/1999/01/reg-watson/\">Dr. Reg Watson</a>. The new and improved version of the database is <a href=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/data/\">now available online</a> and includes updated catch data to 2006, catch reconstructions for China (whose catch was adjusted downward after <a href=\"http://www2.fisheries.com/archive/members/dpauly/journalarticles/2001/systematicdistortionsworldfisheriescatchtrends.pdf\">Watson &amp; Pauly, 2001</a>) and 12 other countries, updated fishing agreements, and improved spatial allocation of catch due to greater knowledge of species distributions.  You can read more about the database updates in the forthcoming Sea Around Us newsletter.</p>','What\'s the Catch? New Fisheries Data Available','','publish','closed','open','','whats-the-catch-new-fisheries-data-available','','\nhttp://www.seaaroundus.org/about/index.php/1999/01/reg-watson/','2010-03-25 08:41:32','2010-03-25 15:41:32','',0,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/?p=1005',0,'post','',0),(1006,2,'2010-03-25 08:37:07','2010-03-25 15:37:07','','FisheriesCatch','','inherit','closed','open','','fisheriescatch','','','2010-03-25 08:37:07','2010-03-25 15:37:07','',1005,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/FisheriesCatch.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1018,2,'2010-03-25 08:54:42','2010-03-25 15:54:42','','10_year_SAU','','inherit','closed','open','','10_year_sau','','','2010-03-25 08:54:42','2010-03-25 15:54:42','',809,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/10_year_SAU.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1038,2,'2010-03-31 11:30:18','2010-03-31 18:30:18','<a href=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/newsletter/Issue56.pdf\"><img src=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Dec09-229x300.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"Dec09\" width=\"229\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1039\" /></a>Read about IUU fishing in the Baltic Sea, get a glimpse at the last 10 years of the Project, and see a summary of the 2009 publications from the <em>Sea Around Us</em> in the <a href=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/newsletter/Issue56.pdf\">November/December newsletter</a>.','November/December 2009 Newsletter','','publish','closed','open','','novemberdecember-2009-newsletter','','','2012-10-04 10:05:51','2012-10-04 17:05:51','',0,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/?p=1038',0,'post','',0),(1039,2,'2010-03-31 11:28:48','2010-03-31 18:28:48','','Dec09','','inherit','closed','open','','dec09','','','2010-03-31 11:28:48','2010-03-31 18:28:48','',1038,'http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Dec09.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1044,2,'2010-04-06 10:15:51','2010-04-06 17:15:51','<a href=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/NatGeoBoat.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-1045\" title=\"NatGeoBoat\" src=\"http://www.seaaroundus.org/about/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/NatGeoBoat-300x193.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"193\" /></a>This week <em>The Sea Around Us</em> Project\'s Daniel Pauly is in the Galapagos Island along with many other notable guests of Mission Blue to fulfill<a href=\"http://www.tedprize.org/mission-blue-voyage/\" target=\"_blank\"> Sylvia Earle\'s 2009 TEDPrize wish</a>. <a href=\"http://www.ted.com/\" target=\"_blank\">TED talks</a>, which is normally hosted in Monterey, California, gathers together remarkable speakers and then makes their talks available online.  This time the