an.com\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicVulcan.gif\" title=\"Vulcan/PGA Family Foundation\"]Vulcan, a Paul G. Allen company, is a nimble private company with a portfolio as diverse as the challenges of the world. Vulcan’s philanthropic group invests in projects that advance discovery and catalyze great ideas that drive positive change for life on the planet.[/grid]\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"/data/#/topic/biodiversity\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicFishbase1.gif\" title=\"FishBase/SeaLifeBase\" target=\"_self\"]Global databases with detailed information on fishes (FishBase) and all other marine organisms (SeaLifeBase).[/grid]\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"http://www.pewtrusts.org/en\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicPew.gif\" title=\"The Pew Charitable Trusts\"]The Pew Charitable Trusts initiated the Sea Around Us and supported it for 15 years, and we continue to collaborate on various initiatives.[/grid]\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"/feru/\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicFERU.gif\" title=\"Fisheries Economics Research Unit\" target=\"_self\"]Long-standing collaboration with the Fisheries Economics Research Unit on all aspects related to fisheries economics.[/grid]\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"/climate-change/\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicChangingOceanResearch.gif\" title=\"Changing Ocean Research Unit\" target=\"_self\"]CORU studies the effects of global climate and ocean changes on marine ecosystems, biodiversity and fisheries, by assessing the biophysical and socio-economic vulnerabilities and impacts of marine climate change, and identifying mitigation and adaptation options.[/grid]\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"http://en.mava-foundation.org/\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/MAVA_LOGO_180px.jpg\" title=\"The MAVA Foundation\"]The MAVA Foundation supports our work in West Africa, and has a dedicated interest in engaging in strong partnerships to conserve biodiversity for future generations.[/grid]\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"http://www.nereusprogram.org/\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicNereus.gif\" title=\"NEREUS\"]The Nereus program developed an international research network able to evaluate future scenarios for managing fisheries in the world’s oceans.[/grid]\r\n\r\n<h1>Sub Projects</h1>\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"/seafoodprint/\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicNationalGeographic.gif\" title=\"National Geographic\" target=\"_self\"]National Geographic supported the Sea Around Us through a common interest in quantifying and illustrating the impact of fisheries on marine ecosystems. We chose the \"seafoodprint\" of fisheries as a measure of this impact.[/grid]\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"/data/#/marine-trophic-index\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicCBD.gif\" title=\"Convention on Biological Diversity\" target=\"_self\"]CBD identified indicators to monitor biodiversity loss, and chose the \'Marine Trophic Index\' (MTI) as one of these indicators. This collaboration developed and presents this indicator by country and LME.[/grid]\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"http://www.balticsea2020.org/english/\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicBalticSea2020.gif\" title=\"Baltic 2020\"]We contributed to the work of the Baltic Sea 2020 Foundation (Sweden) by reconstructing total catch time series for all Baltic Sea countries back to 1950.[/grid]\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"/gapi/\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicGapi.gif\" title=\"Global Aquaculture Performance Index\" target=\"_self\"]The Global Aquaculture Performance Index (GAPI) developed by the Seafood Ecology Research Group at the University of Victoria, Canada, uses a statistical approach to evaluate the environmental performance of marine aquaculture.[/grid]\r\n\r\n[grid link=\"/belize/\" image=\"/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/GraphicOceana.gif\" title=\"Oceana\" target=\"_self\"]Oceana supported a conference held in Belize in 2011 aimed at disseminating and repatriating crucial information on the marine biodiversity and fisheries of Belize 